After much deliberation and regret, we have decided to sell our antique spiral staircase. We bought it originally from Wells reclamation for our home in Blagdon to install there. But all we ever got was to the point of temporary install while I focused on rebuilding the house and garden.

After a few years of that, we got an 'offer we couldn't refuse' and decided to sell our home and buy somewhere else.

We bought a bungalow in Cheddar. What's the one thing you don't need in a bungalow? Yup, you guessed it. A spiral staircase.

So here it sits, in bits, waiting for you to come and pick it up.

I have searched online to try to find pictures of staircases like ours, because I am a bit loathe to put it all together to take pictures and then dismantle it again. I hope you don't mind that. A visit will ensure that you get what you see.

The item is in Cheddar. Please contact us through the Friday Ad platform or call us on 01934 7402...(click to reveal full phone number). Ask for Phil or Jill.

It is black and could do with a new coat of paint. The pictures I found on ebay and other websites are quoting £3000 - 5000. I don't want anything like that, but if I could get back what I paid for it, I think that would be ok by us. Cash is fine, but a bank transfer would work just as well.

So the price reflects what we paid, not what it is worth or probably likely to fetch anywhere else. I hope that means you will get a great bargain.

Just to confirm, the pictures are from the internet and not the actual item. I would hate for anyone to turn up expecting one thing and getting something else. If you own these images and object to my using them please let me know. In any event, I will remove them as soon as the staircase is sold.

I do hope if you are in the market for one of these, you will come and take a look. In these uncertain times, I will wear a mask, and I would hope you would do the same. Thank you for looking.
